└── test-setup/
    └── vitest-setup.ts                   # Global test setup
```

---

## 2. Installation Commands

### Phase 1: Install Playwright (E2E)

```bash
# Install Playwright and browsers
cd /Users/anotonio.silva/antonio/mms/MFC
bun add -D @playwright/test

# Install browsers (required - run with npx, not bunx due to compatibility)
npx playwright install chromium
```

**Critical Note**: Playwright has compatibility issues with Bun runtime. Based on [GitHub issue #27139](https://github.com/microsoft/playwright/issues/27139) and [Bun issue #8222](https://github.com/oven-sh/bun/issues/8222), use `npx playwright test` (not `bunx --bun playwright test`) to avoid hangs and segfaults.

### Phase 2: Install Vitest (Unit/Integration)

```bash
# Root dependencies
bun add -D vitest @vitest/coverage-v8 @vitest/ui

# React testing dependencies (for web app)
bun add -D @testing-library/react @testing-library/jest-dom @testing-library/user-event jsdom

# Happy-dom alternative (faster than jsdom)
bun add -D happy-dom
```

### Phase 3: Install pytest (Python Solver)

```bash
# Navigate to solver and install pytest
cd /Users/anotonio.silva/antonio/mms/MFC/apps/solver
pip install pytest pytest-asyncio pytest-cov httpx
```

Or add to `requirements.txt`:
```
pytest>=8.0.0
pytest-asyncio>=0.23.0
pytest-cov>=4.1.0
httpx>=0.26.0
```

